You know, there's a 99% chance of getting

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:50.600
a check here, so it got
all 100 people got a check.

00:04:50.901 --> 00:04:52.033
Then that would be ...

00:04:52.033 --> 00:04:54.667
Then it would stack it up right over here.

00:04:55.233 --> 00:04:57.834
And so we see using the
assumption that there's

00:04:57.834 --> 00:05:01.566
a 99% chance of the test matching up,

00:05:01.566 --> 00:05:05.433
or there's a 99% chance
that the test is correct,

00:05:05.433 --> 00:05:08.000
it got all of these results.

00:05:08.233 --> 00:05:10.700
And we see that out of
these 100 samples it took,

00:05:10.700 --> 00:05:15.233
none of them, none of
them, gave what Karim

00:05:15.233 --> 00:05:17.000
observed, right over here.

00:05:17.567 --> 00:05:19.966
So it seems like, if you
make this assumption,

00:05:19.966 --> 00:05:22.633
the probability of
observing what he observed

00:05:22.633 --> 00:05:26.667
right over here seems
very, very, very, very low.

00:05:26.966 --> 00:05:30.104
So this, to me or I
guess to any reasonable

00:05:30.104 --> 00:05:32.900
statistician or reasonable
person, these results,

00:05:32.900 --> 00:05:35.633
the results he got, the
results that he both observed

00:05:35.633 --> 00:05:38.633
and the results of the simulation tells us

00:05:38.633 --> 00:05:42.901
that the likelihood of
the hypothesis being

00:05:42.901 --> 00:05:45.467
correct is low.

00:05:45.834 --> 00:05:47.100
So this is a ...

00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:50.412
The likelihood of the
hypothesis that Karim's test

00:05:52.580 --> 00:05:55.233
is correct 99% of the time, the likelihood

00:05:55.233 --> 00:05:57.866
of this hypothesis is very low.

00:05:58.233 --> 00:06:01.633
Very, very, very low.

00:06:01.633 --> 00:06:03.233
Given this observation and the results

00:06:03.233 --> 00:06:04.733
of the simulation.

00:06:04.833 --> 00:06:08.733
And so you'd be likely
to reject the hypothesis.

